  "body": "https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.12.1/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#global-topics\r\n\r\nWe do not ignore blocks that create a new fork from an old (pre-finalization) parent - these block can be produced for example when a node is syncing and is behind the network, but (correctly) creates a block according to its own view of the `head` - by advancing slot of the \"old\" parent to the current wall clock time.\r\n\r\n",
